0
00:00:00,299 --> 00:00:15,419


1
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:30,450
片名：珍珠港

2
00:00:39,090 --> 00:00:41,680
(田纳西州，一九二三年)

3
00:00:59,710 --> 00:01:01,010
德国佬，两点钟方向
German bandits at two o'clock!

4
00:01:01,110 --> 00:01:02,510
全速前进
Increase throttle! Power dive!

5
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:10,050
你拼错了啦，雷夫
Spell it right, Rafe.

6
00:01:10,890 --> 00:01:13,380
方向舵，应该是两个 D
"Rudder" is spelled with two Ds.

7
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,550
谢了，伙伴
哦，不客气
Thanks, wingman. Yeah, sure.

8
00:01:17,330 --> 00:01:18,160
敌机来袭
Whoa, bandits!

9
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:21,850
打得好，丹尼
Crack shooting, Danny.

10
00:01:22,130 --> 00:01:23,030
你也一样
Crack shooting, Rafe.

11
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:24,090
为了自由
Land of the free.

12
00:01:24,270 --> 00:01:25,030
为了祖国
Home of the brave.

13
00:01:44,690 --> 00:01:46,750
飞得帅呆了，老爸
Great flying, Dad

14
00:01:48,790 --> 00:01:51,020
来吧，我教你开飞机
Come on. I'm gonna teach you how to fly.

15
00:01:58,830 --> 00:01:59,730
我要坐前面
I get the front!

16
00:01:59,830 --> 00:02:01,100
不，你得坐后面
No, you take the back.

17
00:02:01,170 --> 00:02:03,100
我比较高，我应该坐前面
I'm bigger, and I should be in front.

18
00:02:03,210 --> 00:02:05,230
我比你大，我还要教你呢
I'm older, and I'm teaching, so no.

19
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:07,240
哇，我们真像在飞一样啦！
Wow. It's like we're really flying.

20
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:09,110
我玩过好几次了
Yeah, I did it lots of times.

21
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:11,200
你去守住机关枪，我来减速
Come on, you man the guns. I'll give her some throttle.

22
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:13,840
我们要打落德国飞机
We gotta get those dirty German bandits.

23
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:20,820
噢，天啊
Oh, gosh!

24
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,430
快停下来，雷夫！
Hang on! Make it stop, Rafe!

25
00:02:31,530 --> 00:02:33,660
我看我爸开过很多次，没事儿！
I've seen my dad do this lots of times, don't worry!

26
00:02:37,110 --> 00:02:37,760
雷夫！
Rafe!

27
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:42,540
喔，我们飞起来了啦！
Oh, my gosh! We're flying!

28
00:02:42,610 --> 00:02:43,600
我们飞起来了
We're flying!

29
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:03,100
我老爸饶不了我！快走
My dad's gonna kill me. Come on.

30
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:06,620
好耶
Yes! Whoo-hoo!

31
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:09,500
我们飞起来了！我们飞起来了！
We flew! We flew!

32
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,770
好耶，我是飞行员
我知道了
Yeah! Yes! I'm a pilot! I know!

33
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:15,870
我们飞起来了
We flew.

34
00:03:15,980 --> 00:03:17,770
你这个没用的东西
爸爸…
You no-account boy! Daddy...

35
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:21,350
我说过，别和这个笨蛋泡在一起
I done told you, you spend time playing with this stupid boy...

36
00:03:21,350 --> 00:03:23,650
他不识字！你会一辈子没出息的
...can't read. you ain't never going to amount to nothing!

37
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:26,220
爸，他才不蠢
He ain't stupid, Daddy!

38
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,650
爸…
Daddy!

39
00:03:29,990 --> 00:03:31,120
过来
Ohh! Come on!

40
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:35,320
马上回家去
Uhh! Get on back home. Now!

41
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:42,120
快点，你还有活要干呢！走吧
Get on up. You got work to do. Come on!

42
00:03:42,670 --> 00:03:44,830
快点，给我回去
Come on, get on home!

43
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:47,970
你放开他
Uhh! You let him alone!

44
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:51,340
爸爸，别这样
Daddy, no!

45
00:03:51,450 --> 00:03:54,070
我要打扁你，你这个臭德国佬！
I will bust you open, you dirty German!

46
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:56,910
你骂我什么？
What'd you call me?

47
00:03:58,620 --> 00:04:00,990
我在法国和德国人打过仗
I fought the Germans in France.

48
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:04,380
非常艰巨的阵地相持战
And I fought them in the trenches.

49
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:09,190
上帝保佑！那些可怕的事情别再发生了
And I pray to God no one ever has to see the things that I saw.

50
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:28,110
你是我最好的朋友
You're my best friend.

51
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:31,440
爸，等等！
Daddy, wait!

52
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:35,180
爸，等等我
Daddy, wait.

53
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:47,830
阿道夫・希特勒把德国变成了战争机器
整个欧洲都陷入了战火
Adolf Hitler builds the German military machine and drags all of Europe into war.

54
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:52,770
即使希特勒占领了法国
但美国仍拒绝加入战局
But even while France falls to Hitler, America still refuses to join the fighting.

55
00:04:53,580 --> 00:04:59,010
(米歇空军基地)

56
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,180
(一九四一年一月，长岛)

57
00:05:10,930 --> 00:05:12,090
麦考利和沃克在哪儿？
Where's McCawley and Walker?

58
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:13,390
还在进行飞行训练
Still training, sir.

59
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:18,660
丹尼！让我们教他们什么叫开飞机
来“老鹰捉小鸡”，准备好了吗？
All right, Danny. Now let's show them how to fly. We're gonna play chicken. You ready?

60
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:22,200
这可不是农场的飞机，我不玩
This ain't the farm, and these ain't no cropdusters. I'm not playing chicken with you.

61
00:05:22,370 --> 00:05:23,930
别当胆小鬼，让我告诉你…
Now don't be a baby. I'll tell you what...

62
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:24,730
我不玩儿，雷夫
I'm not doing it, Rafe.

63
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,930
那我冲你来了，你可以躲开
也可以和我相撞，你看着办吧
Well, I'm coming right at you. You can turn, or you can hit me. It's up to you.

64
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,050
搞什么？
What the...

65
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:33,270
完了
Oh, boy.

66
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,580
你为什么总是害我，雷夫？
Why you always busting my ass, Rafe?

67
00:05:39,350 --> 00:05:40,250
你从哪边过？
Which way you going?

68
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:44,920
我想从右边…不，左边，我从左边
I guess I'll go right. No, uh, left. I'll go left.

69
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:48,520
我们从左边，是吗？
OK, we're going left, right?

70
00:05:48,630 --> 00:05:50,120
嗯，是右边，右边吗？
Ri... uh, right. Right?

71
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:52,060
右边是指我们从右边过
还是指我们从左边过？
Right like we're going right, or right like we're going left?

72
00:05:52,170 --> 00:05:55,400
你把我搅糊涂了！我不知道，你说吧
Well, now you got me all mixed up! I don't know. Make up your mind.

73
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:01,110
上帝啊，雷夫，我们从右边！右边！
God, Rafe, we're going right! Righty-tighty!

74
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,720
他们真是王牌飞行员
Those are some smooth aces.

75
00:06:12,850 --> 00:06:13,750
你说什么？
Did you say something?

76
00:06:14,660 --> 00:06:17,150
我告诉你们，这两个乡巴佬被禁飞了！
'Cause let me tell you, those farm boys are grounded!

77
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:22,290
是的，长官… 决不允许拿军用飞机冒险
Yes, sir, an entirely unacceptable use... of m-m-military aircraft, sir.

78
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:25,160
拿我的帽子来
是的，长官
Get my hat. Yes, sir.

79
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:27,970
叫这些亡命徒去杜立特办公室
Get those hedge-hoppers in Doolittle's office.

80
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,730
已经训练两年了…
After two years of training...

81
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:34,540
你们以为造价四万五千美元的
战斗机是用来玩吗？
you believe that a $45,000 airplane... is there for your amusement?

82
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:37,130
不是，长官，我只是磨练技巧
No, sir. I was just trying... to keep my edge, Major.

83
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:41,610
上礼拜你玩空中翻筋斗
也是为了磨练技巧吗？
And when you did the outside loop last week... what did you think that was? Honing your skills?

84
00:06:41,780 --> 00:06:44,180
那不是飞行技巧！麦考利
是哗众取宠！
That's not training, McCawley. That's a stunt.

85
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:48,560
也是愚蠢和不负责的行为
And I personally consider it to be reckless... and irresponsible.

86
00:06:49,990 --> 00:06:51,550
少校
Major...

87
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,020
怎么会啊，你可是那招的开山鼻祖
How could that be, when you're famous for being the first man in the world ever to do it?

88
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:58,260
别跟我耍嘴皮子
Don't get cute with me, son.

89
00:06:58,330 --> 00:07:02,500
我没有耍嘴皮子，长官
请恕我直言，我只是认为…
No, sir, I don't mean to be disrespectful. I just think that... well, I...

90
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:07,100
如果仅仅只是为了出风头
这是愚蠢和不负责的
It is reckless and irresponsible if you're just doing it to be a show-off.

91
00:07:07,210 --> 00:07:11,170
但我这样是为了启发战友
就像您当初启发我一样
But I was doing it to try to inspire the men, sir... in the way that you've inspired me.

92
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:13,310
有句成语能够用来形容我对您的钦佩
I believe the French even have a word for that...

93
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:16,610
法国人称之为五体投地
when the men get together to honor their leaders. They call it an homage, sir.

94
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,280
什么？
A what?

95
00:07:17,890 --> 00:07:20,250
是五体投地，长官
这全是屁话，麦考利
An homage, sir. That's bullshit, McCawley!

96
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:26,650
但它是很中听的屁话
But it's very, very good bullshit.

97
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:27,820
谢谢你，长官
Thank you, sir.

98
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:34,300
麦考利，你就像十五年前的我
McCawley, you remind me of myself fifteen years ago.

99
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,370
我们现在讨论一下这个
Which is why we need to discuss this.

100
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:38,700
坐下，年轻人
Have a seat, son.

101
00:07:45,950 --> 00:07:48,970
英国人已经接受你加入雄鹰中队
The British have accepted you into the Eagle Squadron.

102
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:53,280
如果你愿意，明天就可以动身
You're on your way to England tomorrow... if you still want to go.

103
00:07:56,260 --> 00:08:00,790
飞行员是英国能否打退希特勒的关键
也决定着欧洲战场的走向
Just a few British pilots are all that stand between Hitler and total victory in Europe.

104
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:02,490
他们非常需要援助
They're gonna need all the help they can get.

105
00:08:02,730 --> 00:08:04,190
我马上出发，长官
Yes, sir. Well, I'm on my way.

106
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:08,330
按照规定，我应该要求你再慎重考虑一下
Just for the record... I'm supposed to ask you to reconsider.

107
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,300
长官？
Sir?

108
00:08:10,370 --> 00:08:11,970
不管我们是否愿意…
Sooner or later we're gonna be in this war...

109
00:08:11,970 --> 00:08:13,470
…美国参战只是时间问题
whether we like it or not.

110
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,010
我们也需要优秀的飞行员
And I'm gonna need all of my best pilots.

111
00:08:16,210 --> 00:08:19,210
所以我应该征询你是否愿意留下来
So it's my duty to ask you to stay.

112
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:22,440
少校，你会怎么做？
Major, what would you do?

113
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:26,520
如果是我…
If it was me...

114
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:30,560
我会去
I'd go.

115
00:08:31,130 --> 00:08:33,280
不会吧，我开始谢顶了？
Get out. Am I going bald right back here?

116
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:38,200
伙计，我是个帅小伙
Man, I am one good-looking son of a bitch.

117
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,390
可千万别死
Don't you ever die.

118
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:44,300
打仗你死不了
今晚你就要装一副快死的样子
Die. That's exactly the concept you gotta work tonight.

119
00:08:45,070 --> 00:08:48,530
往眼睛上抹点儿丁香油
You put a drop of this clove oil under your eyes...

120
00:08:48,740 --> 00:08:53,270
快忍不住的时候就去找护士
做个深呼吸
and you let them sting and well up. You get your nurse alone, take a breath...

121
00:08:54,750 --> 00:09:01,480
然后就热泪盈眶地对她说
宝贝，他们训练我去打仗…
let her see your eyes listen and say, "Baby, they're training me for war...

122
00:09:01,590 --> 00:09:03,780
…我生死难测…
and I don't know what'll happen...

123
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:06,260
…如果明天我一去不返…
but if I die tomorrow...

124
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:11,360
…我盼望今晚我俩能共度春宵
" I want to know that we lived all we could tonight."

125
00:09:11,470 --> 00:09:13,300
来吧，伙计们，漂亮护士在等着咱们
Come on, guys! We got nurses waiting.

126
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:15,960
快点，再不走比利的头就要秃光了
Come on, before the rest of his hair falls out.

127
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:17,830
你为什么要做这样的决定？
How could you do this?

128
00:09:19,810 --> 00:09:23,640
是杜立特点名派我去的
他希望我能够接受实战训练
Well, Doolittle assigned me. He wanted me to get some real... real combat training in.

129
00:09:24,380 --> 00:09:25,470
你想什么呢？
Well, guess what?

130
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:27,910
那儿可没有训练，只有战争
It's not training over there. It's war.

131
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:30,250
输家丢掉性命
赢家也一无所获
Where the losers die, and there aren't any winners...

132
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:32,750
大家都身心疲惫，就像我老爸那样
just guys who turn into broken-down wrecks... like my father.

133
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,890
我知道，我能理解，丹尼
Yeah, I understand that, Danny.

134
00:09:33,890 --> 00:09:35,580
但是我觉得我有责仁去
But I feel like I got a duty to go.

135
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:39,580
见鬼，别和我扯什么责任
我和你一样都是军人
Don't preach to me about duty, damn it. I wear the same uniform you do.

136
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:43,530
如果真有必要，我也会去
可你为什么要这样求之不得？
Now, if trouble wants me, I'm ready for it. But why go looking for it?

137
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:47,760
听我说，丹尼
我快二十五岁了，已经算是个老兵
God, Danny, come on. I'm gonna be twenty-five. I might as well be an old man.

138
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:50,600
我很快就只能当飞行教官了
They're gonna have me being a flight instructor.

139
00:09:50,710 --> 00:09:53,940
我不想当教官，我要开战斗机
I don't wanna teach loops and barrel rolls. I wanna be a combat fighter.

140
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:58,340
快点，护士们在等你们跳舞呢
Hey, come on! The nurses can't d-d-dance by themselves.

141
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,240
我们走吧
Let's go.

142
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:13,220
要是每天都和一百五十个
穿内裤的小伙子们打交道
If the call of duty means seeing 150 men in their underwear every day...

143
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:15,590
我们可不嫌枯燥
...we are here to serve.

144
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:19,130
想不到能在纽约度周末
I can't believe it. Saturday night in New York City.

145
00:10:19,430 --> 00:10:21,200
在家乡太没意思了！
Do you know what they're doing where I come from?

146
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:23,330
什么都不能做，只能逗牛玩
Nothing. Cow-tipping.

147
00:10:24,110 --> 00:10:27,700
所以你来当海军，想开开眼界？
Well, that's why you joined the Navy, hong. To get out of that dusty little town and see the world.

148
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:30,500
巴巴拉，我们是海军护士
可不是来旅游的
May I remind you, Barbara, we're Navy nurses, not tourists.

149
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:34,070
我当海军是来尽义务，还想找个男朋友
I joined to do my patriotic duty and to meet guys.

150
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:36,870
我也是
Me, too.

151
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:38,880
我们今晚玩个痛快！
Girls, we're gonna have so much fun tonight in the city.

152
00:10:38,990 --> 00:10:40,780
给大家讲讲你的故事吧，伊夫琳
You've gotta tell them the story, Evelyn.

153
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:41,910
什么？
What?

154
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:43,620
说呀，告诉我们
Oh, come on. Tell us.

155
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:45,280
噢，说来话长
Oh, it's such a long story.

156
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:46,290
我们时间多的是
We got time.

157
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,990
我亲眼目睹哦
I saw it happen.

158
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,160
那是四个星期前
Well, it was about four weeks ago...

159
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:53,500
你认为怎样更好点？
What do you think is b-b-better?

160
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:56,160
都打在一边，还是分开打？
All in the one cheek, or spreading them out?

161
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:58,400
好吧
OK.

162
00:10:58,510 --> 00:11:00,570
福斯科・安东尼
Fusco Anthony.

163
00:11:05,710 --> 00:11:07,150
你没事吧？老兄
You all right, buddy?

164
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:10,240
甜心，真的要打针吗？
Sweetie, do you really have to do this?

165
